The South African National Blood Service (SANBS), in conjunction with the Western Cape Blood Service (WCBS), have hatched a plan to deliver emergency blood to hospitals by drone.On Wednesday, a TRON Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (UAV) took off from the North Eastern Radio Flyers in Sandton and landed safely, with fake blood, a few minutes later. In the not so distant future , South Africa could see similar flights, delivering real blood, from banks to hospitals. The drones could reach remote areas of South Africa in emergencies. Visit Business Insider South Africa for more on this story.